International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 11 Aug 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID, weekly disease information 2015; 28(33) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18355


African swine fever (ASF), Ukraine
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 Aug 2015 from Dr Oleksandr Verzhykhovskiy, deputy head, State Veterinary and Phytosanitary Service of Ukraine, Ministry of Agrarian Policy and Food, Kiev, Ukraine

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 6 Aug 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 6 Aug 2015
Date event resolved: 9 Aug 2015
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks: (1)
Summary of outbreaks; total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Kharkivtsi village, Pyryatynskyi, Poltova
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 9 Aug 2015
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 277 / 1 / 0 / 277 / 0
Affected population: in the meat from pigs that were imported from farm "Kalyta" (Brovary district, Kyiv region) during the period from 23 to 27 Jul 2015 (before the official diagnosis for ASF in this farm was established). The presence of ASF virus was laboratory confirmed.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: legal movement of animals.
Epidemiological comments: at the slaughterhouse there were a total of 277 carcasses. By the decision of the State Emergency Antiepizootic commission all of the carcasses were destroyed.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs; stamping out; quarantine; movement control inside the country; zoning; disinfection/disinfestation; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; official destruction of animal products; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; dipping/spraying; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone;
no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
State Scientific and Research Institute of Laboratory Diagnosis and Veterinary and Sanitary Expertise (national laboratory) / swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 6 Aug 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Although the current outbreak has been determined to be resolved, there is little doubt that African swine fever (ASF) continues to circulate in Ukraine.

Since June of 2014, Ukraine has reported ASF in the regions of Chernigov, Sumy, Kiev, Rovno, and Zhitomir. All outbreaks reported in Ukraine from 1 Jan 2014 to date, can be seen in the interactive map at http://tinyurl.com/pqe9atd (click on the section of interest on the map, and zoom in).

A map of Ukraine's administrative divisions can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/maps/Ukraine-Administrative-Map.jpg and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3573464,47421. - Mod.CRD]
